The paper deals with the construction and analysis of codes for multimedia fingerprinting, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves the study of bounds on the number of codewords, which is related to coding theory (cs.DS). The specific application of strongly separable codes makes it relevant to multimedia systems (cs.MM) and coding theory (cs.CC).
